The paper discusses a method for extracting features from datasets for use in machine learning algorithms. The method focuses on capturing local structure and uses both geometric and topological features at multiple levels of granularity. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of geometric and topological features suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Finally, the use of machine learning algorithms suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
